headline: 2 Dow Jones Dividend Stocks With Yields Above 3% You Can Buy Now and Hold at Least a Decade
summary: If you have any faith in economic indicators, right now seems like a terrible time to buy stocks.  A long bull market has pushed the major market indices up to record highs.  As a result, the S&P 500's cyclically adjusted price-to-earnings ratio, or CAPE ratio, recently shot up past 35 for the third time in more than 150 years.
